notes.name: IMDS Reference
steps: A#{ A/C Tail } - See all jobs

IFLT - Flight roster
On Equipment Supply
Screens Training
Off Equipment

notes.name: Forms
steps:
X is the highest (non-flyable condition),
- When replacement is due or OPs checks. Flyable condition
/ when minor discrepancy exists. Still flyable condition
A main job cannot be signed off unless all WCE's have been signed off

A dash is higher than a diagonal. Since dashes are an unknown conditions and diagonals are a minor condition, the dash is higher because we dont know if its bad or not.

notes.name: IMDS Usage
steps: Print Margins: 0.6 left, 0.4 right, 0.8 top, 0.8 bottom

Pulling 781A
- 320 screen to suppress (Main jobs dont have a WCE, suppress that. If there is no WCE's then dont suppress it. Stop when K's are reached)
- 255 screen to print

- In the old A's, put end date and last page number, Check 'CF 781A', Sign Corrected By

Transfer A - K
- 54 screen
- Event ID (JCN)
- Defer Code (Reason awaiting action)
- Equipment ID

notes.name: Troubleshooting
steps:
Delta-P extends during launch
- Reset
- If it does not extend after reset: Good
- If it does not reset: Bad, shutdown

<6 Fuel pump lights
- Remove door 3308
- Unscrew black lense cap (ensure the bulb comes with it)
- Switch with a known working bulb
- If it still does not light up: shutdown
- If it does light up, note the bulb will need to be replaced, close 3308.

BIT fail
- Cycle flight controls until B system hydro is above 55 degrees.
- If fails again, cycle until 70-75 degrees
- If it still fails, call for a red ball

notes.name: Hydraulics
steps:
A system:
- LEFs
- Flight Controls
- Speed Brakes
- FFP

B System:
- Flight Controls
- LEFs
- Landing Gear
- Nose Wheel Steering
- Gun
- AR Door
- Brakes
- JFS
When case drain filter is replaced, an engine run is required for a bleed and leak because it only has hydro in it when the pump is running

notes.name: Fuel
steps:
- F-1: Directly behind the cockpit (bladder)
- F-2: In front of AR door
- Forward Reservoir: right side of AR door
- Aft reservoir: left of AR door
- A-1: Under dorsal fairing

Full fuel loads:
- Slick: 7,200 lbs
- Centerline: 9,200 lbs
- Wing tanks: 12,200 lbs
- Wing tanks + centerline: 14,000 lbs

flyer-ff: Forms (781 H, A, K, J) Remember required inspection
Power On (Check fuel, LOX, and lights)
flyer-pl: Remove nose gear pin and arresting hook pin
Setup cockpit (survival straps over lap belts)
Have forms ready for when pilot arrives
flyer-pr: Hand pilot CDU cover and HUD cover before he gets out
Write down fuel load, LOX, and Oil
flyer-th: Fuel, Oil, and LOX loads into 781H
flyer-ed: Write down Fuel, LOX, and oil
job: Find job in TO, find follow on MX
Write up main job and follow on MX jobs
Accomplish job, Read TO, Especially for the install.
Sign off jobs and follow on MX that was accomplished
towing: Confirm umbilical cord is not attached on pylons
Fuel pylons decarted (Safety wired or backwards)
LOX bottle removed if moving to Fuels
Wind >30 Knots: minimize canopy use. Wind >50 Knots: do not open canopy
>1000 lbs of weight on nose required
